  Best MVP Build Order

  I would implement in this exact order:

  1. Extension shell and Canvas route detection.
  2. Current page collector.
  3. Base, assignment, page, syllabus, and module parsers.
  4. Chunking and keyword retrieval.
  5. Prompt builder with citations.
  6. canvasChatMode current-page-only.
  7. Source chips and provider disclosure UI.
  8. Short-lived cache with TTL and clear controls.
  9. Current module collection.
  10. Privacy/security hardening.
  11. PDF/file parsing.
  12. Optional embeddings.

  The key engineering discipline is to get “current assignment question with citation” working before broadening scope. That path exercises detection,
  collection, parsing, retrieval, prompt construction, model streaming, citations, and privacy rules without introducing crawler complexity too early.




      